BuildStep
/ Builds a step that needs detailed action info
/ Action suggestions (module + action) already on step from BuildGoal
- set %step% = %goal.Steps[stepResult.index]%
- goal.getTypes Goal=%goal%, write to %variablesByStep%
- set %variables% = %variablesByStep[stepResult.index]%
- render template "/system/builder/llm/BuildStep.user.llm", write to %stepForLlm%
- render template "/system/builder/llm/BuildStep.actionDetails.partial.llm", write to %actionDetails%
- render template "/system/builder/llm/BuildStep.system.llm", write to %buildStepPrompt%
- set %messages% = [{"Role":"system", "Content":"%buildStepPrompt%"}, {"Role":"user", "Content":"%stepForLlm%"}], type=json
/ Wrap llm.query + Validate together so the retry surface catches BOTH
/ malformed-JSON (llm.query throws) and validator failures (type-name guard,
/ unknown action, missing required param). BuildStepFixer re-prompts with
/ the error message; runtime retries the wrapped goal up to 2 times.
- call QueryAndValidateBuildStep, on error call BuildStepFixer, then retry 2 times

QueryAndValidateBuildStep
- llm.query Messages=%messages%, Schema={errors?: [{key: string, message: string}], warnings?: [{key: string, message: string}], actions: [{module: string, action: string, parameters?: [{name: string, value?: object, type?: string}], errors?: [{key: string, message: string}], warnings?: [{key: string, message: string}]}]}, cache=%!build.cache%, write to %result%
- add {stepIndex: %stepResult.index%, stepText: %step.Text%, level: %stepResult.level%, system: %buildStepPrompt%, user: %stepForLlm%, response: %result%} to %trace.detailPasses%
- save %trace% to file '/.build/traces/%!trace.id%/%trace.goal.name%.json'
- call ValidateBuildStepResult
- set %goal.Steps[stepResult.index].Actions% = %result.actions%
- builder.validate actions=%goal.Steps[stepResult.index].Actions%

BuildStepFixer
/ LLM produced invalid output for a step — retry with error context
- write out "  Step validation failed: %!error.Message% — retrying..."
- set %messages% = [{"Role":"system", "Content":"%buildStepPrompt%"}, {"Role":"user", "Content":"Your previous response had validation errors:\n%!error.Message%\n\nThe step to build:\n%stepForLlm%\n\nFix the errors above and return the complete corrected response."}], type=json

ValidateBuildStepResult
/ Check for top-level and action-level errors from the BuildStep LLM
- if %result.errors% is not empty, call ThrowBuildStepErrors
- foreach %result.actions%, call ValidateActionErrors, item=%action%

ThrowBuildStepErrors
- throw error "BuildStep failed for step '%step.Text%': %result.errors%"

ValidateActionErrors
- if %action.errors% is not empty, call ThrowActionErrors

ThrowActionErrors
- throw error "Action %action.module%.%action.action% failed for step '%step.Text%': %action.errors%"

HandleBuildStepFailure
- write out "  Build step error: %!error.Message%"
- throw %!error%
